HEADWORD: To-name
<hw>To"-name`</hw> <pr>(t⟦oomac⟧"n⟦amac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[prep. <ets>to</ets> + <ets>name</ets>.]</ety> <def>A name added,
for the sake of distinction, to one's surname, or used instead of
it.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

